00:00:11,634 --> 00:00:11,701
I feel like you've been talking for like a year.

184
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:14,334
Honey, all this stuff I'm telling you is important.

185
00:00:15,801 --> 00:00:15,868
It's all part of the story.

186
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:17,200
Could I go to the bathroom?

187
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:18,634
No.

188
00:00:22,801 --> 00:00:22,868
The summer of 2006 was both wonderful and awful.

189
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:25,534
For me, it started out great.

190
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:27,167
In fact, day one was amazing.

191
00:00:29,234 --> 00:00:31,234
I'd finally gotten together   with Robin.

192
00:00:32,701 --> 00:00:32,767
But while I'd been off having   one of the best nights

193
00:00:34,968 --> 00:00:35,033
of my life, your uncle Marshall

194
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:38,067
had been having one   of the worst nights of his.

195
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:40,834
* Crying in the street... *

196
00:00:41,801 --> 00:00:41,868
MARSHALL:  So that's it?

197
00:00:43,801 --> 00:00:43,868
We're breaking up?

198
00:00:45,601 --> 00:00:45,667
Marshall, I'm sorry. I just...

199
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:47,200
I just need to go

200
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:50,167
to San Francisco and do this art program and-and figure out

201
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:52,334
who I am outside of us.

202
00:00:53,934 --> 00:00:54,000
And the only way

203
00:00:58,701 --> 00:00:58,767
that I can do that is if... if we don't talk for a while.

204
00:01:00,701 --> 00:01:00,767
For a while.

205
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:02,167
Try never, okay?

206
00:01:05,834 --> 00:01:05,901
You walk out that door, and we're done.

207
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:08,434
You're never going to hear my voice again.

